# Project context

## What this is

- **Portfolio purpose:** Show **creativity, innovation, front-end craft, design, and rich coding** to **potential clients** — focus on **freelance or periodic work** (not a generic tutorial site).
- **In-universe product:** A **credible fictional festival brand** with a **real festival landing experience** (not a thin “portfolio frame” site).
- **Planning:** **FigJam** moodboards and structure are the reference for vibe and modules; repo work should align with that direction.

## Language

- **Public UI and all user-facing copy:** **English** (even if FigJam notes are PT-BR).
- **Decorative texts:** **German, korean, portuguese, japanese, arab** (handle different charsets).
- **Code comments and agent ↔ dev chat:** English unless the user switches.

## Must-have experience (from brief + FigJam)

- **Hero** — strong first read, typographic / image-led, room for **grain, tint, glitch-adjacent** treatments.
- **TV news–style ticker / marquee** — horizontal **scrolling announcements** for **party / rave news** (repeatable strip, bold type, configurable accent on dark bar is on-brand).
- **Lineup** — **fake but curated** (consistent names, genres, times; treat like production content).
- **Motion & depth:** **Full scene–level section changes**, **dynamic text animations**, **mouse-driven layout** where **pointer movement rearranges or drives text** on screen (plus optional **mouse-trail character** effects from the board).
- **Audio** — part of the experience (respect autoplay policies; offer clear user control).
- **Optional later (FigJam):** **Three.js**–style **3D graffiti / exhibition panels** (“galeria exposição”) — add when implementing that milestone, not by default in every task.

## Visual & creative direction

- See **`.cursor/rules/design-identity.mdc`** for aesthetic keywords, palette, and references (maximal type, B&W + neon accents, urban/editorial).

## Stack & libraries

- **Core:** **Nuxt 4**, **Vue 3**, **TypeScript**.
- **Extra tech:** Any dependency is allowed when it serves the build — **no blanket ban** on new tools (Three.js, extra animation libs, font pipelines, etc.); keep integrations **bounded** and **documented in code** when non-obvious.
- **Showcase libs (use when they earn their place):**
  - **`@fiddle-digital/string-tune`** — music / string / tuning interactions.
  - **[Pretext.js](https://pretextjs.dev/)** (`@chenglou/pretext`) — layout/measurement **without DOM measurement thrashing**; `prepare()` uses **Canvas** → **client-only** (`<ClientOnly>` / `onMounted`) under SSR.
  - **Three.js** — only for the **3D graffiti / panel** idea from FigJam; load in a bounded client-only island.
- **Not the default stack:** React, Next.js, Tailwind — only if explicitly introduced to the repo.

## Performance & shipping

- **Target:** **High-performance devices** first (desktop / strong phones); still avoid obvious jank and layout thrashing.
- **Deploy:** **Static** (`nuxt generate` / static hosting) is **desired** — prefer patterns compatible with **SSG**; heavy interactivity lives in **client islands** without breaking the static build.

## Principles

- Prefer **small, targeted changes**; avoid unrelated refactors.
- **Match** existing patterns in the repo; **reuse** composables and components.
- Do **not** add unsolicited README/docs unless the task is documentation.
- **Accessibility:** semantic HTML, focus, **respect `prefers-reduced-motion`** where motion is decorative; don’t ship motion-only critical info.

## When unsure

- Re-read **design-identity** + this file; check **`nuxt.config.ts`** and **`app/`** / **`pages/`** before inventing new structure.
